   1 $group
   2     e transformer
   3         # A model transformer .
   4         # The ittf node value is the transformer name {wizzischema}/{transformer}
   5         # to be found in {wizziPackage}/artifacts/{wizzischema}/{transformer}/trans/main.js
   6         a_tag( dumpFile,  dump-file )
   7             # A filepath where the transformed model must be dumped for test.
   8             # When declared the transformed model is JSON.stringyfied and written
   9             # to the "dumpFile" filepath.
  10         r comment/s
  11     e artifact
  12         # Describe an artifact to be generated.
  13         # It is a child element of a "line" element.
  14         #
  15         # Can be one of:
  16         # . A Wizzi model instance, acting as a template, which WizziSchema targets a code language technology.
  17         # . A swig template.
  18         # . A code write generation that takes in input a context of one or more WizziModels.
  19         # . A final artifact to be copied to a destination folder without transformations.
  20         # . A reference to another WfJob, to be executed before the current WfJob where the artifact is declared.
  21         #
  22         # Context value objects for template transformations are declared in the "model" element, child of the "wfjob" root element
  23         # and may be referenced in the elements "modelRef", children of the "artifact" element.
  24         #
  25         # The "src" or "destPath" attributes of an "artifact" element may contain tokens enclosed in graph parens.
  26         # When one of the "modelRef@" is a collection model, the artifact generation is repeated
  27         # for each item of the collection and the "src" or "destPath" attributes become the template of the destination path.
  28         # See the "pathTemplateValues" child elements of the "modelRef" for the values that will replace the tokens.
  29         #
  30         # Example
  31         #
  32         # artifact
  33         # dest-path app/db/{table}Datalayer.js.ittf
  34         # ...
  35         # model-ref rdbms
  36         # model-coll tables
  37         # item-name table
  38         # path-template-value
  39         # attribute tableName
  40         # token table
  41         #
  42         # model rdbms
  43         # ...
  44         #
  45         # the Wizzi model instance after loading rdbms: {
  46         # ....

   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Reads an IttfDocument and extract an array of line descriptions
   6     #
   7         # Input
   8         # param textContent:String - The text content of the IttfDocument
   9         # param ittfDocumentData:Object {
  10         # sourceKey:String - The IttfDocument key generated by the loadContext
  11         # }
  12     #
  13         # Output
  14         # lines:Array of
  15         # line : {
  16         # indent: Number,
  17         # name: String,
  18         # value: String, // always trimmed
  19         # row: Number,
  20         # col: Number,
  21         # sourceKey: String,
  22         # tagSuffix: undefined || '(',
  23         # hasMacro: Boolean
  24         # }
  25     #
  26         # Ittf commands for comments
  27         # $ and $ ... singleline comment
  28         # $ and * ... * and $ multiline comment
  29         # Comment states
  30         # 0 = no comment seen
  31         # 1 = seen char $ could be first char of comment
  32         # 2 = seen chars $ and * we are inside multiline comments
  33         # 3 = seen chars $ and * ... and *  could be first char of end of multiline comments
  34         # 21 = seen chars $ and $ we are inside singleline comment
  35         # Es6 macro states
  36         # 0 = no macro seen
  37         # 1 = seen char ` we are inside macro
  38         # 2 = seen escape char inside a macro, the next ` char does not close the macro string
  39     set module.exports
  40         function
  41             param textContent
  42             param ittfDocumentData
  43             var
  44                 decl sourceKey = ittfDocumentData.sourceKey
  45                 decl lines
  46                     [
  47                 decl leadingWhiteSpaces = 0
  48                 decl line = null
  49                 decl linepos = 1
  50                 decl lineHasMacro = false
  51                 decl colpos = 0
  52                 decl commentState = 0
  53                 decl macroState = 0
  54                 decl quote = null
  55                 # TODO ensure textContent is red as utf-8 and avoid this
  56                 decl chunk = textContent.toString('utf-8')
  57                 decl ch
  58                 decl chUni
  59                 decl i
  60                 decl l = chunk.length
  61             # TODO replace ch with chUni
  62             for i = 0; i < l; i++
  63                 set ch = chunk[i]
  64                 set chUni = chunk.charCodeAt(i)
  65                 set colpos++
  66                 if quote != null
  67                     if quote == ch
  68                         set quote = null
  69                     _ processMacro(ch)
  70                 else
  71                     if commentState == 2
  72                         if ch == '*'
  73                             # could be start of end of comment
  74                             set commentState = 3
  75                         else
  76                             # skip comment char
  77                             if ch == '\n'
  78                                 set linepos++
  79                                 set colpos = 0
  80                     elif commentState == 21
  81                         if ch == '\n'
  82                             # end of line comment
  83                             # delegate end of comment to processMacro
  84                             _ processMacro(ch)
  85                     elif commentState == 3
  86                         if ch == '$'
  87                             # ok, really is end of comment
  88                             set commentState = 0
  89                         else
  90                             # no, comments continue
  91                             set commentState = 2
  92                             # check if it is eol
  93                             if ch == '\n'
  94                                 set linepos++
  95                                 set colpos = 0
  96                     elif commentState == 1 && ch == '*'
  97                         # ok, really is start of comment
  98                         set commentState = 2
  99                     elif commentState == 1 && ch == '$'
 100                         # ok, is a line comment
 101                         set commentState = 21
 102                     elif commentState == 1 && ch != '*'
 103                         # no, it was not a comment, reset
 104                         set commentState = 0
 105                         _ processMacro('$')
 106                         _ processMacro(ch)
 107                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == '"'
 108                         # start of literal
 109                         set quote = ch
 110                         _ processMacro(ch)
 111                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == "'"
 112                         # start of literal
 113                         set quote = ch
 114                         _ processMacro(ch)
 115                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == '$'
 116                         # could be start of comment
 117                         set commentState = 1
 118                     else
 119                         _ processMacro(ch)
 120             if line
 121                 if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 122                     set line.value = line.value.trim()
 123                 set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 124                 _ lines.push(line)
 125                 set lineHasMacro = false
 126             return lines
 127             function processMacro
 128                 param ch
 129                 if macroState == 2
 130                     # remove escape state
 131                     set macroState = 1
 132                     # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 133                 else
 134                     if chUni == 96
 135                         if macroState > 0
 136                             set macroState = 0
 137                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 138                         else
 139                             set macroState = 1
 140                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 141                     else
 142                         if macroState == 1
 143                             if ch == '$'
 144                                 set ch = '#'
 145                                 set lineHasMacro = true
 146                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 147                             elif ch == '\\'
 148                                 # could be an escape of a macro inside a macro
 149                                 set macroState = 2
 150                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 151                 _ processChar(ch)
 152             function processChar
 153                 param ch
 154                 if ch == '\n'
 155                     if line
 156                         if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 157                             set line.value = line.value.trim()
 158                         set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro

   4     #
   5         # Nodify the lines of an IttfDocument and creates a
   6         # tree structure object based on line indentation.
   7         # . detects the $params command
   8         # . implements line continuation
   9         # . assigns an id to each node
  10         # !!! A line object is transformed in place into a node object
  11         # without recreation (no cloning) !!!
  12         #
  13         # Inputs
  14         # - the lines produced by the liner
  15         # Outputs
  16         # nodes: Array of [
  17         # line -> mTreeNode : {
  18         # + parent: Object, // parent mTreeNode
  19         # + model: Object, // the MTree to which the line belongs
  20         # + children: Array, // the children mTreeNodes
  21         # id: Number,
  22         # indent: Number,
  23         # name: String,
  24         # value: String,
  25         # row: Number,
  26         # col: Number,
  27         # sourceKey: String,
  28         # tagSuffix: undefined || '('
  29         # hasMacro: Boolean
  30         # }
  31         # ]
  32         #
  33         # Ittf commands:
  34         # $params  // the param values are stored in the MTree
  35         # \        // implements line continuation
  36         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  37         # //   without separators
  38         # \b       // implements line continuation
  39         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  40         # //   with a space separator:  prevLine,value += ' ' + currentLine.value
  41         # \n       // implements line continuation
  42         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  43         # //   with a line break separator:  prevLine,value += '\n' + currentLine.value

  93                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && nameLength == 1
